Frequently used tcpdump commands
================================

>>	tcpdump -i <interface-name> :- Sniff on particular interface

>>	tcpdump -w <filename.pcap> :- Stored sniffed packet info in file

>>	tcpdump -tttt :- Proper readable timestamp

>>	tcpdump -i <interface-name> dst/src <ip> and port <num> :- Commonly used display filter
